Results._refObjectName: As an admin user, I can create/read/update/delete a product record and its attributes
Results.Description:
Acceptance Criteria:

  • Only admin users may access the CRUD product UI. Non-admin users are redirected to an "unauthorized", user-friendly error page.
  • Users can add, edit, and delete one product at a time.
  • Product Fields:
    • Name (required)
    • Alternate Name (optional)
    • Designation (required)
    • Summary (optional)
    • Inactive Date (optional)
  • Users can associate or disassociate attributes with each product.


Detailed User Stories

CREATE_PRODUCT:  As an admin user, I want to create a new product record so:

  • I navigate to the 'Add/Edit Products' shown under the System Administration Menu (note - only shown if I'm admin)
  • The system shows a screen allowing me to select a product or to add a new product
  • I select add a new product
  • The system prompts me to enter a name (required), designation (required), summary, and alternate name for the product
  • The system adds the newly created product to the list of products to edit and preselects it
  • The system displays a list of master attributes for all products (grouped appropriately) and allows me to select the ones i want to initially add to the product
  • (Step #7) I select 'Edit Product' (note - this is only enabled if a product is selected)
  • The system creates the product and assigns the selected attributes to it
  • The system shows me a grid edit for the product showing all attributes (Name, value, unit of measure, source) where I can edit value, unit of measure and source for each
    • For LIST types of attributes, I'm constrained to picking values from a multilist
    • For BOOLEAN values, I'm constrained to setting a checkbox
    • For DATE values. I'm constrained to picking a valid date (calendar control)
    • For FILE/IMAGE values - I'm constrained to picking a file/image via an upload dialog (upload from my local machine
  • I can press the Add/Remove attributes button to change the attributes attached to the product
    • The system presents a popout showing the list of attributes (as previously shown in the filter)
    • I can select/deselect what I want to add/remove
    • When done - I press 'OK"
    • The system returns to the product grid edit with the appropriate attributes added/removed
    • ALT:  I can press 'CANCEL' and return to the product grid edit as before (no changes made)
  • I can press the Comparison/Competitor button to add/remove competitors & comparable products
    • The system presents a popup showing the list of comparable & competing products
    • I can select/deselect what I want to add/remove
    • The system returns to the product grid edit with the appropriate competitors/comparables added/removed
    • ALT:  I can press 'CANCEL' and return to the product grid edit as before (no changes made)
  • I can press the Clone button to make a copy of this product
    • TODO:  How to handle clone?
  • (Step #13)When I'm finished I press Save
  • ALT:  If I navigate away from the page without having pressed save - the system does not save the added/changed product or associate it with any competitors/comparables
  • The system validates the data
    • TODO:  put validation information here

READ/UPDATE_PRODUCT:  Ads an admin user, I want to view and/or edit an existing product so:

  • I navigate to the 'Add/Edit Products' shown under the System Administration Menu (note - only shown if I'm admin)
  • The system shows a screen allowing me to select a product or to add a new product
  • I select a product from the dropdown list of all products
  • {Proceed from step #7 in CREATE_PRODUCT - the system does not create a new product in step #8, but rather retrieves the existing product/data}

DELETE_PRODUCT:  Ads an admin user, I want to delete an existing product so:

  • Proceeds as READ/UPDATE_PRODUCT
  • At Step #13, an alternative course is to press the 'Delete' button
  • The system confirms that I meant to delete the product
  • If I confirm, the Product is marked as deleted and no longer appears in any product lists and is no longer editable/accessable
  • If I dont confirm, I return to READ/UPDATE_PRODUCT
Results.Name: As an admin user, I can create/read/update/delete a product record and its attributes

Results._refObjectName: As a user, I can subscribe to, view, and modify all of my subscription so that I know when data changes on select reports.
Results.Description:
From R6s doc:

When a user creates a report, upon saving it, they will have the option to be notified if a piece of data on their report changes. The user can select a time frame for how long the notification will apply for (ex. 30 days, 90 days, 1 year, etc). Users can easily unsubscribe via the email received for a data change. (Unsubscribe and Unsubscribe All)

From Sprint Planning:

Report Subscriptions: Add an icon to the Report History grid items that will tell the user whether or not something on that report has changed. Along with this feature would be the ability to resync the report with an "Resync to Database Value" button. The "Resync " button is greyed out if there is no newly changed data for the report. Warning will be displayed if there are custom edits. Custom edits will not resync. When running a report, add a new report option checkbox for "Notify me of changes" defaulted to true along with a timeframe drop down (30/60/90 days). Add the ability to unsubscribe.

Product Subscriptions: Users will also have the ability to explicitly subscribe to products without having to run a report. These subscriptions are the ones that drive the email.
Results.Name: As a user, I can subscribe to, view, and modify all of my subscription so that I know when data changes on select reports.

Results._refObjectName: As an admin user, I can view and edit requests for data changes submitted by users
Results.Description:
Add ability to add products, attributes, and values.

Back end data should be easily updatable to the Operations Research team.

When saving the data the data steward should have 2 options surrounding notifications. These options are only available for saving data values outside of the data change request workflow.
1) Notify for subscriptions

Fields:
Product (from the request) (view in grid)
Attribute (from the request) (view in grid)
Old Value (from the request)
New Value (from the request)
Source (from the request)
Reason (from the request)
User that requested (from the request) (view in grid)
Admin that is working it
Status (view in grid)

Comments - a multi-line text box for free form comments.
Created Date (read-only) (view in grid)
Last Modified Date (read-only)

New
Under Review (pending)
Accepted (Closed)
Declined (Closed)

Buttons:
Assign to Me: this button changes to the Admin that is working it field to logged in user
Save
Cancel

By default, only display New and Under Review in the grid view. Have the ability to display all, regardless of status.

Results._refObjectName: SubFeature: Interactive report view in HTML
Results.Description:
Requirements notes:

  • Each field should be editable prior to clicking "Generate"
    • Example: cost varies with qty and cost assumption may need to change   displayed for a particular purpose.
    • Every field editable prior to generating the pdf/csv
  • Interactive HTML View
    • Toggle units of measurement
    • Request/flag an attribute and value to be changed:
      • Adds the request to a table
      • Request must include: Desc, New Value, and New Source
      • Products, attrib, and values.
      • Notification to Admins
    • Ability to hide an attribute
    • Print Preview after this stuff changes
    • Edit values that only are displayed on this report

Results._refObjectName: As a user, I can save my report to a dynamically created RShare location that will be viewed in the ITP app
Results.Description:
Requirements notes:

User clicks "Send to ITP"

PCD web app checks to see if logged User has an ITP Rshare directory under the "PCD Reports" folder.

If they do have an ITP directory, then write the file.

************************************************************************************************************
NOT FEASIBLE. ALL PCD USERS WOULD NEED TO BE ADMINS IN ITP TO ACHIEVE THIS
************************************************************************************************************
If they don't have an ITP directory (see attached screenshot):
Create a folder for the user with the foldername = Peoplesoft IT.
Give the RShare "PCD Reports Admins" user group "Contribute" permissions the new folder.
Give the RShare "RMS LT Administrators" user group "Full Control" permissions to the new folder.
Give the logged in user "Contribute" permission on this folder.
Then write the file to the new folder.
************************************************************************************************************

The app itself, the may need ITP Approved Users role.
Results.Name: As a user, I can save my report to a dynamically created RShare location that will be viewed in the ITP app

Results.Name: As a user, I can email the report to myself using a RefApp 5 microservice

Results._refObjectName: As an RMS user, I need to access PCD in a limited fashion without too much burden on the PCD admin user in order to view product information.
Results.Description:
From Bob's perspective, if you have a Raytheon badge you have a "need to know" basis for viewing product information. This alleviates the concern for RP213 (Raytheon Proprietary material) compliance.

If one or two attributes need to be hidden to the average "everyone" user, then those products need to be configurable as hidden by an admin user.

Consider Levels of users:

  • General User
  • Capture User
  • Admin User

Also consider the ability to add users at the org level to the Capture User level.


RP 213 Text snippet:



Access to Raytheon Most Private, Raytheon Proprietary, and Raytheon Competition Sensitive information is

restricted to only those individuals who require knowledge of the information in order to perform activities

necessary for the business interest of Raytheon. Raytheon Most Private, Raytheon Proprietary, and Raytheon

Competition Sensitive information should not be posted on the Raytheon Intranet or other electronic systems

without suitable access controls.
Results.Name: As an RMS user, I need to access PCD in a limited fashion without too much burden on the PCD admin user in order to view product information.
